Finger tracking can be emulated with controllers such as the Index controllers, but some headsets with '[https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/mixed-reality/enthusiast-guide/tracking-system inside-out tracking]' such as the Meta Quest, or Pico, can also utilize finger tracking. Finger tracking is currently supported on Pico, and all Meta Quest headsets, and can be used with either standalone VR, or through PCVR. The feature originally launched in [[Special:MyLanguage/Open Beta|Open Beta]] on October 26, 2022, for Meta Quest systems, and was publicly released for 2022.4.1<ref>[https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202241 'VRChat 2022.4.1'] on ''docs.vrchat.com''; retrieved May 3, 2025</ref>, on November 3, 2022.